This paper is about neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a new decoding algorithm for neural machine translation models, which involves training a generative network using the Gumbel-Softmax reparameterization. This approach is related to reinforcement learning and optimization, which are also subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses empirical evaluation to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed model, which involves training and testing neural networks, a common practice in the field of neural engineering (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
